Parliament, Monday, 19 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Rural Development and Land Reform will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Department of Rural Development and Land Reform on the Mala Mala land claim; a status report on commonage programmes; a status update on the Rama Communal Property Association; the Riemvasmaak Trust and the report on land transfers and issuance of title deeds to successful land claimants and beneficiaries of land redistribution. Date: Tuesday, 20 March 2018 Time: 10h00
	Venue: Committee Room 3, 90 Plein Street. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON RURAL DEVELOPMENT AND LAND REFORM, MS PHUMUZILE NGWENYA-MABILA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sureshinee Govender
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 2289
